# Verify After Changes

After making changes to this project, run `npm run check` to ensure the app still compiles and lints. Run `npm run verify` for larger changes.

## When to run check (every change)

- Any edit to the codebase
- Layout, styling, API, globals.css, tailwind.config changes = always run check

## When to run verify (full build)

- Schema changes (Prisma, env)
- New features or multi-file edits
- Adding or removing dependencies
- API or component refactors

## What to do

1. Run `npm run check` after edits (from project root: `touring-crew-app`)
2. Run `npm run verify` for schema changes, new deps, multi-file refactors
3. If verify or check fails: fix the reported errors before finishing
4. If Prisma schema changed: also run `npx prisma generate` and `npx prisma db push` before verify

## Commands

- `npm run check` – TypeScript + lint only (faster, use after most edits)
- `npm run verify` – TypeScript + lint + build (full check)
